      "title": "Reading 1",
      "content": "Many language learners believe that having a native accent is important. However, English has many different regional varieties, even within the same country. Therefore, learners should first think about their main goal for learning the language.\n\nInstead of trying to imitate a specific native accent, it is much more useful to practice understanding different speakers. Today, English is used worldwide as a global medium of communication. Because of this, even native speakers now take courses to learn how to understand international varieties of English.\n\nUltimately, English no longer belongs only to native speaking countries; it belongs to the whole world. Being a good English user today means being an effective communicator who can understand different cultures, rather than just having a perfect native accent."
    },
